{"questionId":"27810","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>DeVaughn throws a javelin in a school track and field competition.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/cdd45b709d6f7d19966199a7c8a9633d21aa0806.png\"></p>\n<p>The height, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math>, of the front tip of the javelin above the ground, in metres, is modelled by the&nbsp;following quadratic function,</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> is the time in seconds after the javelin is thrown.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> when the front tip of the javelin reaches its maximum height.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp;seconds&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)A0</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>)</mo></math> seen.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27810","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.3b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the value of t when the front tip of the javelin reaches its maximum height.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.5—Intersection of lines, equations of perpendicular bisectors","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Voronoi diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}